This paper is about natural language correction using a neural network approach, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a recurrent neural network with an attention mechanism suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of additional data to improve performance, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
